<br>
Add in pvp kills too score and see who wins. Try fighting for almost every zone or mob you want. So many factors you need you lack for a truthful study. You in no way allowed a fair and equal scoring system for the diff servers. Its alot easier to sign a list and zone into PoH, WW, or PoH with no threat of pvp move on to your guild objective. Try fighting through forces almost equal to your own, using only the gear your able to get by fighting other players for, and doing your whole raid while keeping ready for the fact that someone else could come along and challenge you for your zone. <br>
<br>
Even each member of the pvp server guilds has to fight harder for what he has. Be it gear or exp. These players in some cases like Team PvPers are restricted from having the best race/classes or even whole classes, yet still doing what others do. So what if it takes them longer, or harder to do it. IMO that just proves that its that much harder to do on PvP servers. Xanit K Ven might not have been first to kill Inny, but by god they did it with PURE evils. No bards, druids, no rangers, no monks. Cleared the plane using SKs to feign death pull and fought tooth and nail to get to him. Silent Souls/Prophets, the 4 team guild on VZ might have the edge of having all classes on a raid. But that too comes with draw backs. They can not use AEs, have pkers attack from all teams, and fight a two sided war against the Evils, and the now Lightie team. Yet they still do great things, like killing the Dain. Then you have the 3 team light side. Whos strongest guild is Defiant. They miss out on having AEs, Troll/Orge Tanks, and other advantages of pure blue servers. They must fight for zones from the other sides, and even the Purist team lighties who stick to the 4 Team system. Even with the lack of gear blue servers enjoy and basic freedom of movement, Defiant has killed CT twice now, completed 6 Warrior epics, 2 Mage epics, 1 Wizard epic, 6-7 Ranger epics, 5 Druid epics, 5 Rogue epics, 2 Bard epics, 7 Shaman, 2 Pally epics, 7 Cleric epics and 3 Ench epics (based of current in guild, not people who left, or people outside guild Defiant has helped).<br>
<br>
IMO your system might be legit (not even sure how you score) if we all played on blue servers. But fact is there are 3 pvp servers out there. And each one has great guilds who go through more than any blue guild yet do not get the same respect. Even little things like faction hits from pvping players can get in the way of PvP server guilds from doing what blues can do. Also pvp server players are slowed down from developing because of the side stream of pvp that goes on. Taking them longer to reach the points blues are at, not because lack of skill, but because time taken from pvp. Look at all a pvp player must learn and go through to get his character higher. He must learn to play his class atleast well in pvp, or face lots of CR time, taking more time from his pve or bluebie activities of character advancement.<br>
<br>
Just the view from a person who has been on Team PvP server almost his whole EQ time. Maybe some day you will come up with a diff scoring system to take in account the diff of blue and pvp servers. Or maybe you will come up with a diff system to rate pvp guilds on a diff chart than blues.<br>
<br>
